%N A393609 Square array A read by descending antidiagonals: A(n,k) = prime(A035513(n, k)).
%C A393609 Every prime occurs exactly once. Every row and every column is strictly increasing.
%F A393609 A(n,k) = A000040(A035513(n, k)).
%F A393609 a(n) = A000040(A035513(n)).
%e A393609 Corner:
